rlQosServ.description: The MIB module describes the private MIB for QOS service mode.

rlQosServTemplateTable.name: rlQosServTemplateTable
rlQosServTemplateTable.description: This table specifies classification template information. Currently this table will contain exactly one entry.

rlQosServTemplateEntry.name: rlQosServTemplateEntry
rlQosServTemplateEntry.description: The entry of this table describes all classifier fields. The index is sequential integer represent by rlQosServTemplateEntry.

rlQosServTemplateIndex.description: An arbitrary index for the template table.

rlQosServTemplateSrcMac.name: rlQosServTemplateSrcMac
rlQosServTemplateSrcMac.description: Include the source Mac field as a template classifier.

rlQosServTemplateDestIpMask.name: rlQosServTemplateDestIpMask
rlQosServTemplateDestIpMask.description: Destination Ip address mask. It may specify any byte (not bit), within the Ip address, for classification, designated by 0.

rlQosServTemplateSrcIp.name: rlQosServTemplateSrcIp
rlQosServTemplateSrcIp.description: Include the source Ip field as a template classifier.

rlQosServTemplateSrcIpMask.name: rlQosServTemplateSrcIpMask

rlQosServTemplateIpProtocol.name: rlQosServTemplateIpProtocol

rlQosServFclTable.name: rlQosServFclTable
rlQosServFclTable.description: This table specifies FCL table information

rlQosServFclEntry.name: rlQosServFclEntry
rlQosServFclEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes one Flow Classification List with It's Flow Classification Element. The information includes the FCL index and reference to a FCE index. The indices are the Fcl index represent by rlQosServFclIndex and the Fce index represent by rlQosServFclFceIndex.

rlQosServFclIndex.name: rlQosServFclIndex
rlQosServFclIndex.description: An arbitrary index for the FCL table. Value '0' is invalid.

rlQosServFclFcePriority.name: rlQosServFclFcePriority
rlQosServFclFcePriority.description: Priority of the FCE within the FCL.

rlQosServFclFceIndex.name: rlQosServFclFceIndex
rlQosServFclFceIndex.description: A reference to the FCE index.

rlQosServFclStatus.name: rlQosServFclStatus
rlQosServFclStatus.description: The status of a table entry. It is used to delete/Add an entry from this table.

rlQosServFceTable.name: rlQosServFceTable
rlQosServFceTable.description: This table specifies FCE table information

rlQosServFceEntry.name: rlQosServFceEntry
rlQosServFceEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes one Flow Classifier Element. The information includes ACE index and a combination of all the other classifications, as depicted in the selection field. Classifiers are Mac and Ip source and destination addresses, Vlan, Ip protocol, TCP & UDP source and destination ports, Dscp and Ip precedence values. The index is a sequential integer represent by rlQosServFceIndex.

rlQosServFceIndex.name: rlQosServFceIndex
rlQosServFceIndex.description: An arbitrary incremental Index for the Fce table.

rlQosServFceDestMac.name: rlQosServFceDestMac
rlQosServFceDestMac.description: Indicates the destination Mac address to compare with.

rlQosServFceDestMacMask.name: rlQosServFceDestMacMask
rlQosServFceDestMacMask.description: Indicates the destination Mac address mask to compare with. It may specify any byte (not bit), designated by 0.

rlQosServFceSrcMac.name: rlQosServFceSrcMac
rlQosServFceSrcMac.description: Indicates the source Mac address to compare with.

rlQosServFceSrcMacMask.name: rlQosServFceSrcMacMask
rlQosServFceSrcMacMask.description: Indicates the source Mac address mask to compare. It may specify any byte (not bit), designated by 0.

rlQosServFceVlan.name: rlQosServFceVlan
rlQosServFceVlan.description: Indicates the Vlan to compare with.

rlQosServFceVlanMask.name: rlQosServFceVlanMask
rlQosServFceVlanMask.description: Indicates 12-bits Vlan bits to compare. It may specify any byte (not bit), designated by 0.

rlQosServFceDestIp.name: rlQosServFceDestIp
rlQosServFceDestIp.description: Indicates the destination Ip address to compare with.

rlQosServFceDestIpMask.name: rlQosServFceDestIpMask
rlQosServFceDestIpMask.description: Indicates the destination Ip address mask to compare. It may specify any byte (not bit), designated by 0.

rlQosServFceSrcIp.name: rlQosServFceSrcIp
rlQosServFceSrcIp.description: Indicates the source Ip address to compare with.

rlQosServFceSrcIpMask.name: rlQosServFceSrcIpMask
rlQosServFceSrcIpMask.description: Indicates the source Ip address mask to compare. It may specify any byte (not bit), designated by 0.

rlQosServFceIpProtocol.name: rlQosServFceIpProtocol
rlQosServFceIpProtocol.description: Indicates the Ip protocol to compare with.

rlQosServFceDestPort.name: rlQosServFceDestPort
rlQosServFceDestPort.description: Indicates the TCP/UDP destination port to compare with.

rlQosServFceDestPortMask.name: rlQosServFceDestPortMask
rlQosServFceDestPortMask.description: Indicates 16-bits TCP/UDP destination port bits to compare. It may specify any byte (not bit), designated by 0.

rlQosServFceSrcPort.name: rlQosServFceSrcPort
rlQosServFceSrcPort.description: Indicates the TCP/UDP source port to compare with.

rlQosServFceSrcPortMask.name: rlQosServFceSrcPortMask
rlQosServFceSrcPortMask.description: Indicates 16-bits TCP/UDP source port bits to compare. It may specify any byte (not bit), designated by 0.

rlQosServFceDscp.name: rlQosServFceDscp
rlQosServFceDscp.description: Indicates the Destination Mac address to compare with.

rlQosServFceIpPrecedence.name: rlQosServFceIpPrecedence
rlQosServFceIpPrecedence.description: Indicates the Ip precedence to compare with.

rlQosServFceVpt.name: rlQosServFceVpt
rlQosServFceVpt.description: Indicates the VPT to compare with.

rlQosServFceVptMask.name: rlQosServFceVptMask
rlQosServFceVptMask.description: Indicates the VPT mask to compare with. It may specify any bit, designated by 0.

rlQosServFceEtherType.name: rlQosServFceEtherType
rlQosServFceEtherType.description: Indicate the Ether Type to compare with.

rlQosServFceTcpFlags.name: rlQosServFceTcpFlags
rlQosServFceTcpFlags.description: Indicates the Tcp Flags field to compare with.

rlQosServFceTcpFlagsMask.name: rlQosServFceTcpFlagsMask
rlQosServFceTcpFlagsMask.description: Indicates the Tcp Flags field to compare with.

rlQosServFceIcmpType.name: rlQosServFceIcmpType
rlQosServFceIcmpType.description: Indicates the Icmp type to compare with.

rlQosServFceIcmpCode.name: rlQosServFceIcmpCode
rlQosServFceIcmpCode.description: Indicates the Icmp code to compare with.

rlQosServFceIgmpType.name: rlQosServFceIgmpType
rlQosServFceIgmpType.description: Indicates the Igmp type to compare with.

rlQosServFceStatus.name: rlQosServFceStatus
rlQosServFceStatus.description: The status of this table entry. It is used to delete/Add an entry from this table.

rlQosServProfileTable.name: rlQosServProfileTable
rlQosServProfileTable.description: This table specifies (service) profile table information

rlQosServProfileEntry.name: rlQosServProfileEntry
rlQosServProfileEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes one service profile element. The information includes: Profile name, type and various numeric parameters associated with the profile's service types. The index is sequential integer represent by rlQosServProfileIndex.

rlQosServProfileIndex.name: rlQosServProfileIndex
rlQosServProfileIndex.description: An arbitrary index for the profile table.

rlQosServProfileIngressBurstSize.name: rlQosServProfileIngressBurstSize
rlQosServProfileIngressBurstSize.description: Profile's Ingress Burst Size, used only by the 'rate limit' service.

rlQosServProfileMaxBandwidth.name: rlQosServProfileMaxBandwidth
rlQosServProfileMaxBandwidth.description: Profile's Max Bandwidth, used by the 'min delay', committed delay' 'min max bandwidth' and committed Bound Bandwidth'services. Value 0 is used only as default value, and is invalid otherwise.

rlQosServProfileMinBandwidth.name: rlQosServProfileMinBandwidth
rlQosServProfileMinBandwidth.description: Profile's Min Bandwidth, used only by the 'min max bandwidth' service. Value 0 is used only as default value, and is invalid otherwise.

rlQosServProfileMaxDelay.name: rlQosServProfileMaxDelay
rlQosServProfileMaxDelay.description: Profile's Max Delay, used only by the 'committed delay' service. Value 0 is used only as default value, and is invalid otherwise.

rlQosServProfileStatus.name: rlQosServProfileStatus
rlQosServProfileStatus.description: The status of a table entry. It is used to delete/Add an entry from this table.

rlQosServServiceTable.name: rlQosServServiceTable
rlQosServServiceTable.description: This table specifies service table information.

rlQosServServiceEntry.name: rlQosServServiceEntry
rlQosServServiceEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes one service profile element. The information includes: service's index, priority, pointers to associated profile and Fcl, operational and administrative statuses, ingress and egress interface lists, and two operational parameter values associated with a service type, as defined in the profile table. The index is sequential integer represent by rlQosServServiceIndex.

rlQosServServiceIndex.name: rlQosServServiceIndex
rlQosServServiceIndex.description: An arbitrary index for the service table.

rlQosServServiceInIfList.name: rlQosServServiceInIfList
rlQosServServiceInIfList.description: Ingress interface list associated with this service entry.

rlQosServServiceOutIfList.name: rlQosServServiceOutIfList
rlQosServServiceOutIfList.description: Egress interface list associated with this service entry.

rlQosServServiceScaledOutIfList.name: rlQosServServiceScaledOutIfList
rlQosServServiceScaledOutIfList.description: Egress scaled interface list associated with this service entry.

rlQosServServiceProfileParamOper.name: rlQosServServiceProfileParamOper
rlQosServServiceProfileParamOper.description: If the service type specified in a profile associated with this entry has a parameter, this object instance specifies the parameter's operative value. This value will be different from the value defined in the associated profile only in case of scaling out, otherwise value 0 is used.

rlQosServServiceStatusOper.name: rlQosServServiceStatusOper
rlQosServServiceStatusOper.description: Operational value of the service status.

rlQosServServiceStatusAdmin.name: rlQosServServiceStatusAdmin
rlQosServServiceStatusAdmin.description: Administrative value of the service status.

rlQosServServiceStatus.name: rlQosServServiceStatus
rlQosServServiceStatus.description: The status of a table entry. It is used to delete/Add an entry from this table.

rlQosServServicePriorityTable.name: rlQosServServicePriorityTable
rlQosServServicePriorityTable.description: This table specifies service priority table information.

rlQosServServicePriorityEntry.name: rlQosServServicePriorityEntry
rlQosServServicePriorityEntry.description: Each entry in this table maps a priority to a service. The information includes: service's priority and the service index in the service table. The index is sequential integer represent by rlQosServServicePriorityIndex.

rlQosServServicePriorityPointer.name: rlQosServServicePriorityPointer
rlQosServServicePriorityPointer.description: The index of the service associated with this priority in the service table.

rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingTable.name: rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingTable
rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingTable.description: This table specifies service priority table information.

rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingEntry.name: rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingEntry
rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes one service priority entry. The information includes: service's priority, a pointer to its corresponding index in the service table. The index is sequential integer represent by rlQosServServicePriorityIndex.

rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingType.name: rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingType
rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingType.description: Service type for the default mapping. 'Trust DSCP' service type is absent since no default mapping is possible for it.

rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingDscp.name: rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingDscp
rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingDscp.description: DSCP default mapping value. A value of 64 means no DSCP default mapping is done.

rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingVpt.name: rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingVpt
rlQosServServiceDefaultMappingVpt.description: Vpt default mapping value. A value of 9 means no VPT default mapping is done.

rlQosServScalingErrorTable.name: rlQosServScalingErrorTable
rlQosServScalingErrorTable.description: This table specifies scaling error table

rlQosServScalingErrorEntry.name: rlQosServScalingErrorEntry
rlQosServScalingErrorEntry.description: Each entry in this table specifies for each interface its scaling error, if such indeed exists.

rlQosServFreeSequentialTable.name: rlQosServFreeSequentialTable
rlQosServFreeSequentialTable.description: The table is used to get free indices of tables to create new entries, and next free priorities. The algorithm for free indexes depends on table types: Fcl table - first free index. Fce table - first free index. Service table - first free index. Service priority - last used priority + priority-delta. The priority-delta is used to supply QoS MIB user easy new priority insert entry capabilities. Values of these deltas depend on the MIB implementation. The 'Get and Increment' approach is used in all cases.

rlQosServFreeSequentialEntry.name: rlQosServFreeSequentialEntry
rlQosServFreeSequentialEntry.description: The entry is used to get free index for particular table.

rlQosServFreeSequentialId.name: rlQosServFreeSequentialId
rlQosServFreeSequentialId.description: Identification of the sequential, for which free indices or priority are retrieved.

rlQosServFreeSequentialValue.name: rlQosServFreeSequentialValue
rlQosServFreeSequentialValue.description: The free index for the table or service priority. Returned '0' means no free entries/priority.

rlQosServNameToIndexTable.name: rlQosServNameToIndexTable
rlQosServNameToIndexTable.description: The table is used to get specific table(s) indices from the name.

rlQosServNameToIndexEntry.name: rlQosServNameToIndexEntry
rlQosServNameToIndexEntry.description: The entry is used to get index form particular name and table type.

rlQosServNameToIndexTableId.name: rlQosServNameToIndexTableId
rlQosServNameToIndexTableId.description: Identification of the table, for which the index is retrieved.

rlQosServNameToIndexValue.name: rlQosServNameToIndexValue
rlQosServNameToIndexValue.description: The index of the table. Value '0' is invalid.

rlQosServNameToIndexStatus.name: rlQosServNameToIndexStatus
rlQosServNameToIndexStatus.description: The status of a table entry. It is used to delete/Add an entry from this table.

rlQosServIndexToNameTable.name: rlQosServIndexToNameTable
rlQosServIndexToNameTable.description: The table is used to get specific table(s) name from indices. It is a read-write table for internal (CDB) purpose only and is not to set by outside users.

rlQosServIndexToNameEntry.name: rlQosServIndexToNameEntry
rlQosServIndexToNameEntry.description: The entry is used to get name form particular index and table type.

rlQosServIndexToNameTableId.name: rlQosServIndexToNameTableId
rlQosServIndexToNameTableId.description: Identification of the table, for which the name is retrieved.

rlQosServIndexToNameIndex.name: rlQosServIndexToNameIndex
rlQosServIndexToNameIndex.description: The index of the table. Value '0' is invalid.
